From: gt-be98 open-OS migration <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-06-06
Subject: [PATCH] syslogd: honor default (auto) local logging in the read loop

busybox 1.37.0 syslogd, when built with CONFIG_FEATURE_REMOTE_LOG=y,
silently drops every message received on /dev/log from the local logfile
unless -L (or -R) is given explicitly.

syslogd_init() captures getopt32()'s result into the local `opts` and then
auto-enables "log locally" when no -R was given via:

        option_mask32 |= OPT_locallog;        (global only)

but returns the *local* `opts`, which was snapshotted before that bit was
set. The main read loop then gates local logging on the stale local copy:

        if (!ENABLE_FEATURE_REMOTE_LOG || (opts & OPT_locallog))
                split_escape_and_log(...)

so the auto-locallog bit is never seen and split_escape_and_log() is never
called for received messages (only the synchronous startup banner is
written, via timestamp_and_log_internal()).

This is a regression vs busybox 1.25.1, whose equivalent read-loop gate
tested the *global* option_mask32 (and thus honored the auto bit). The
sibling remote-forwarding check at line ~906 already uses option_mask32 in
1.37.0; the local-logging gate was the only inconsistent reader.

Effect on GT-BE98: ASUS rc start_syslogd() passes "-m 0 -S -O <logfile>
[-s SIZE] [-l LEVEL]" and only adds -L when nvram log_ipaddr is set
(remote syslog server configured). In the default case (no remote server),
neither -R nor -L is present, so our substituted syslogd received messages
on /dev/log but never appended them to /jffs/syslog.log.

Fix: gate the read loop on option_mask32 (matches 1.25.1 and the sibling
check), so the auto "log locally by default" actually takes effect.

Verified under qemu-arm with the exact ASUS argv (no -L): both a raw
/dev/log datagram and `busybox logger` output now append to the logfile.

Signed-off-by: gt-be98 open-OS migration <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 sysklogd/syslogd.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/sysklogd/syslogd.c
+++ b/sysklogd/syslogd.c
@@ -1179,7 +1179,7 @@ int syslogd_main(int argc UNUSED_PARAM, char **argv)
 			}
 		}
 #endif
-		if (!ENABLE_FEATURE_REMOTE_LOG || (opts & OPT_locallog)) {
+		if (!ENABLE_FEATURE_REMOTE_LOG || (option_mask32 & OPT_locallog)) {
 			recvbuf[sz] = '\0'; /* ensure it *is* NUL terminated */
 			split_escape_and_log(recvbuf, sz);
 		}
